featured_reviews.review_id:
A small but quite a mosque to offer salah five times on regular days, while it gets quite over crowded on Friday.

Well,  The Hazrat Bilal mosque is situated deep inside Tugalpur basti. The ways to get there are sometimes not much cleaned always. But you can make it to get there.
The mosque is not quite big but definitely multi storey accommodating good number of Namazis in Friday prayer. While on five times a day,  the ground floor is full and almost the second floor.  But yes,  the scenery is quite good in Ramdhan.  Every floor is full in Taraweeh.

Talking about mosque architecture, it's small but wittiy design as the West direction is not parallel or right angle to the road rather making 45 angle in between. So the mosque is well structured according to that.

Well, if you are searching for the sect of the mosque,  then sorry my friend, i won't mention and either i don't care.  We folks have created the sects.  And let's not divide the mosque on the same basis.

featured_reviews.review_id:
This is a very big Mosque ( Ma Sha Allah). Thousands of people can offer prayer at a time.Very soothing , calm and quite atmosphere. Such a great tranquility is felt here. The Mosque is easily noticeable as it is located on the road side. Ample space for car/bike parking is also available in the Mosque's premises. But if you are late, you can park your car across the road in the service lane near to Honda Showroom. But please don't park your car on the main road. It has been often seen that even when there is space in the Mosque premises, some brothers tend to park their cars on the main road causing disturbance to traffic. This request is made by Imam Sahab every Friday but still some brothers continue to park their cars on the main road.

I am attaching Namaz time table. Khutba e Jummah is at 1:00 PM.

Other option nearby available for Juma is the Mosque in Noida Authority Muslim Qabristan (~1.5km). Khutba Juma at Qabristan mosque is at 13:30 hrs.
